\v 13 a silver dish that weighed one and one-half kilograms and a silver bowl that weighed four-fifths of a kilogram. Both of these were full of good flour and mixed with olive oil to be flour offerings. They were both weighed using the standard scales.
\v 14 He also brought a small gold dish that weighed 14 grams and was filled with incense,

\ts\*
\li
